label: Opened breweries
title: Brewery boom
chatter: After Dayton signed the “Surly Bill” into law in 2011, which opened the door for brewers to serve beer on site, the number of craft breweries in the state exploded.

label: New business filings
title: Boom in business filings
chatter: The number of new business filings in Minnesota each year has increased significantly.

label: Wolf population
title: Stabilized wolf population
chatter: Since the Minnesota DNR began conducting annual wolf population estimates in 2005, the number of wolves in the state has stabilized in the last few years after falling significantly in the previous decade.

label: Foreign-born population
title: Increased immigrant population
chatter: The percentage of Minnesota's foreign-born population has steadily increased over the years.
source: U.S. Census Bureau, Minnesota State Demographic Center

label: Population of color
title: A diversifying state
chatter: Minnesota's population of color has steadily increased over the years.
source: U.S. Census Bureau, Minnesota State Demographic Center

label: Broadband access
title: Increasing broadband Internet access
chatter: The percentage of Minnesota households with access to high-speed broadband Internet has steadily increased since it started being closely tracked by efforts to improve connectivity across the state.
source: Minnesota DEED, Connected Nationa, Governor's Taskforce on Broadband

label: Median income
title: Median household income
chatter: Minnesota's median household income reached a low point during the Great Recession but has been rebounding since its end.

label: UMN 4-year graduation rate
title: UMN four-year graduation rate
chatter: The University of Minnesota's four-year graduation rate has been gradually improving over time.
source: University of Minnesota Office of Institutional Research

label: Walleye population
title: Rebounding walleye population
chatter: The walleye population of Lake Mille Lacs has been a hot political topic in Minnesota during Dayton’s tenure. Minnesota’s DNR has allowed catch-and-release fishing only for state-licensed anglers for the past three summers, to allow the walleye population to rebuild.

label: Jobs
title: Steady increases in available jobs
chatter: The total nonfarm payroll jobs in Minnesota has gradually risen since the end of the Great Recession.

label: Good roads
title: Improvements to road quality
chatter: The percentage of roadways rated as having good ride quality by MNDOT has increased after some years of stagnation.

label: Incarceration rate
title: Minnesota state prison incarceration rate
chatter: Minnesota's state prison incarceration rate has been rising steadily for years, even after a slight decrease near the beginning of Dayton's administration.

label: Percent with public insurance
title: More use of public health insurance
chatter: The percentage of Minnesotans with health insurance from a public provider has increased in the passage of the Affordable Care Act.

label: Traffic delay hours
title: Increasing hours in traffic
chatter: The hours spent by commuters in traffic each year was rising drastically before stabilizing in the Pawlenty years.
source: Texas A&M Transportation Institute, Urban Mobility Scorecard

label: Metro population
title: Booming metro population
chatter: The population of the Twin Cities metro area has been steadily increasing.
source: U.S. Census Bureau, Minnesota State Demographic Center

label: Outstate population
title: Less growth in Greater Minnesota
chatter: Population growth in Greater Minnesota's rural and outstate areas has been more stagnant than the metro area the last couple decades.
source: U.S. Census Bureau, Minnesota State Demographic Center

label: Graduation rate
title: Rising high school graduation rates
chatter: Minnesota's overall high school graduation rate has been gradually increasing.

label: Math proficiency
title: Stagnant eight grade math proficiency
chatter: The percentage Minnesota eighth graders achieving math standards has been relatively flat since 2011.

label: Adults working
title: Stabilized percent of adults in workforce
chatter: The percentage of Minnesota adults aged 16 to 64 in the workforce dipped during the Great Recession before rebounding.

label: UMN tuition
title: Climbing University tuition
chatter: In-state resident tuition at the University of Minnesota had been increasing steadily until a tuition freeze deal with the Legislature in 2013.
source: University of Minnesota Office of Institutional Research

label: Obesity
title: Stagnant statewide obesity
chatter: The percentage of Minnesotans older than 19 who are obese has remained relatively flat over the years.
source: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention

label: College degrees
title: More college-educated Minnesotans
chatter: The percentageof Minnesotans with a bachelor's degree or higher has increased steadily over the years.

label: Open enrollment
title: Open enrollment
chatter: Since the introduction of open enrollment in Minnesota's schools back in 1993, the percentage of students attending districts outside of their own has gradually increased.

label: Median age
title: An aging state
chatter: Minnesota's median age has slightly increased over the years.
source: U.S. Census Bureau, Minnesota State Demographic Center

label: Diabetes
title: Stagnant diabetes diagnoses
chatter: The percentage of Minnesotans older than 19 who are diagnosed with diabetes has remained relatively flat over the years.
source: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention

label: Six-year graduation rate
title: Increased college graduation rate
chatter: The six-year graduation rate at Minnesota's four-year colleges and universities has gradually increased over time.

label: Educational spending
title: Stagnant state school funding
chatter: The percentage of school funding coming from the state has remained fairly stagnant over the years.

label: GDP
title: Rebounding state GDP
chatter: Minnesota's annual change in gross domestic product bounced back after the Great Recession but has been steady since.

label: UMN enrollment
title: Steady University of Minnesota enrollment
chatter: The University of Minnesota's fall semester enrollment has remained steady over time.
source: University of Minnesota Office of Institutional Research

label: Undergraduate loans
title: Undergraduate loans
chatter: The cumulative total of undergraduate student loans in Minnesota had been climbing steadily for years before declining and flattening toward the end of Pawlenty's administration.

label: Reading proficiency
title: Stagnant third grade reading proficiency
chatter: The percentage Minnesota third graders achieving reading standards has been relatively flat since 2013.

label: Volunteerism
title: Declines in volunteerism
chatter: The percentage of Minnesotans aged 16 or older who volunteed in the past year has declined over the years.
source: U.S. Census Bureau, Minnesota State Demographic Center

label: Poverty
title: Declining poverty
chatter: The percentage of Minnesotans in poverty was rising for awhile before starting a decline after the Great Recession.

label: Elderly with disabilities
title: Slight decline in elderly disabilities
chatter: Thepercentage of Minnesotans aged 65 or older with a disability has slowly declined.

label: Homeownership gap
title: Reduced homeownership gap
chatter: The homeownership gap – the percent difference between white residents and those of color who own homes – spiked during the Great Recession before leveling off.

label: Poor highways
title: Fewer miles of poor highways
chatter: The percentage of highways rated as having poor ride quality by MNDOT has gradually decreased.

label: Health uninsurance rate
title: Declining health uninsurance rate
chatter: Minnesota's health uninsurance rate has dropped since the 2009 federal passage of the Affordable Care Act.

label: Congested lane miles
title: Less traffic congestion
chatter: The percentage of Twin Cities lane miles congested during rush hour has slightly decreased over time.
source: Texas A&M Transportation Institute, Urban Mobility Scorecard

label: Greenhouse emissions
title: Greenhouse emissions reductions
chatter: As measured in tons, greenhouse gas emissions have slightly declined statewide since 2011.

label: Homelessness
title: Increases in homelessness
chatter: The number of Minnesotans experiencing homelessness has increased over the years, but has seen a slight decline recently.

label: Cost-burdened housing
title: Cost-burdened housing
chatter: The share of cost-burdened Minnesota households paying 30 percent or more of their income on housing costs swelled over the Pawlenty administration before gradually declining under Dayton.

label: Mental health admissions
title: Mental health admissions
chatter: The rate of psychiatric hospital admissions per 1,000 Minnesotans aged older than 13 has slightly decreased over the years.
source: Minnesota Hospital Association, National Center for Health Statistics

label: Crime rate
title: Plummeting crime rates
chatter: Minnesota's statewide crime rate has fallen steadily over the past two decades.

label: River pollution
title: Fluctuating amounts of river pollution
chatter: Levels of phosphorous pollution by metric tonnage in the Mississippi and Minnesota rivers has has slightly decreased over the past set of five-year averages.

label: Traffic casualties
title: Fewer traffic injuries and fatalities
chatter: The rate of traffic injuries and fatalities per 100,000 residents has declined in Minnesota the past couple decades.
source: Minnesota Department of Public Safety, National Highway Traffic Safety Administration, U.S. Census Bureau

label: Moose population
title: Stabilized moose population
chatter: Minnesota’s moose population is stable after a decade-long decline, but shows no signs of recovery, according to the Minnesota DNR’s aerial moose survey, which has been conducted annually in northeastern Minnesota since 2013.

label: Traffic over bad bridges
title: Less traffic over deficient bridges
chatter: The percentage of urban traffic traveling over structurally deficient bridges in Minnesota has decreased significantly since the collapse of the 35W Bridge.

label: Unemployment rate
title: Plummeting unemployment
chatter: Minnesota's unemployment rate has declined drastically since the end of the Great Recession in 2009.

label: White unemployment
title: Crashing white unemployment
chatter: Unemployment rates among Minnesota's white population has decreased significantly since the end of the Great Recession.

label: Black unemployment
title: Crashing black unemployment
chatter: Unemployment rates among Minnesota's black population has decreased significantly since the end of the Great Recession.

label: Hispanic unemployment
title: Crashing Hispanic unemployment
chatter: Unemployment rates among Minnesota's Hispanic population has decreased significantly since the end of the Great Recession.

label: State budget forecasts
title: From deficit to surplus
chatter: The Pawlenty years were characterized by significant state government budget forecasts transitioned from deficits to surpluses during the Dayton administration. The incoming governor, Tim Walz, will inherit a $1.5 billion budget surplus.
